<seg id=1> Indonesian Police Summon Reporter for Trial, Accused of Releasing Information on Woman's May Insurrection Violation. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Jakarta AFP) "Protecting reporters committee", an international organization to champion news freedom, expressed surprise that Indonesian police summoned a reporter for trial, regarding the release of news about Chinese women violated in May's insurrection. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Protecting reporters committee, whose office in New York, said that reporter Gonavan serving for the magazine "Jakarta-Jakarta" was summoned to Police Headquarters for cross-questioning on Thursday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The committee said that, Gonnavan cited the words of one violated woman in a report published in July. </seg>
<seg id=5> A report published in The New York Times on June 10th cited the words of the same victim. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the letter written by the committee to Indonesia President Habibi, it reads that issuing summons was "the first step of police to accuse". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The committee "worries much about the negative effect on freedom of speech for adducting such an law." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The committee referred to the fact that Indonesian Islam organizations applied pressure on the government and to arrest Gonavan, according to the Article 156 of the Criminal Code. </seg>
<seg id=9> The article forbids people to slander religious organizations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> The International Independent Reporter Association also protested the police decision to summon Gonavan. </seg>
<seg id=11> It said that this will "set a precedent, and weaken freedom of speech the most since ex-president of Suharto handed down the reins of leadership." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Protecting reporters committee urged Habibi to "stop mistreating Gonavan", and demanded each party to settle the issue in civil court. </seg>
<seg id=13> It also appealed to each party to "try their best to eliminate the Articles relating to slander in the Indonesian Criminal Code". </seg>
</p>
